Metadata Endpoints: The Crown Jewel
Why Metadata Endpoints Are Extremely Dangerous

Metadata endpoints are internal APIs exposed by cloud providers to VMs, containing:

    IAM credentials (can control entire cloud account)

    SSH keys (direct server access)

    User data (startup scripts, secrets)

    Network configuration (internal topology)

Cloud Provider Metadata Endpoints
Provider	Endpoint	Critical Data
AWS	http://169.254.169.254/latest/meta-data/	IAM roles, user-data, SSH keys
GCP	http://metadata.google.internal/computeMetadata/v1/	Service accounts, access tokens
Azure	http://169.254.169.254/metadata/instance?api-version=2017-08-01	Managed identity credentials
Alibaba	http://100.100.100.200/latest/meta-data/	RAM role credentials
DigitalOcean	http://169.254.169.254/metadata/v1/	Droplet metadata
Kubernetes	https://kubernetes.default.svc/	Service account tokens
