Why These Endpoints Are So Dangerous

1. No Authentication Required
bash

# Anyone on the VM can access metadata
curl http://169.254.169.254/latest/meta-data/
# Works without any credentials!

2. Permanent Until Rotated

    IAM credentials last 6 hours minimum

    Some tokens last 12+ hours

    User-data persists forever

3. Privilege Escalation

    Metadata often has high-privilege IAM roles

    Can control entire AWS account

    Access to all resources (S3, EC2, RDS, Lambda)

4. Chain Reaction
